BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
To solve this inequality, we add [`5`] to each side.

[```\newcommand{\addright}[1]{{\highlight{{{}+#1}}}}\newcommand{\gt}{>}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
x-5\amp\gt-4\\
x-5\addright{5}\amp\gt-4\addright{5}\\
x\amp\gt1
\end{aligned}
```]

Graphically, we represent this solution set as:

>> [@image(insertGraph($image_1), width=>600)@]*  <<

Using interval notation, we write the solution set as [`(1, \infty)\text{.}`] Using set-builder notation, we write it as [`\newcommand{\gt}{>}\{x \mid x \gt 1\}\text{.}`]

We should check that some number less than [`1`] is _not_ a solution, that [`1`] itself is _not_ a solution, and that some number greater than [`1`] _is_ a solution.

[```\newcommand{\substitute}[1]{{\color{blue}{{#1}}}}\newcommand{\confirm}[1]{\stackrel{\checkmark}{#1}}\newcommand{\reject}[1]{\stackrel{\text{no}}{#1}}\newcommand{\wonder}[1]{\stackrel{\text{?}}{#1}}\newcommand{\gt}{>}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
\amp\amp x-5\amp\gt-4\amp\amp\\
\substitute{0}-5\amp\wonder{\gt}-4\amp \substitute{1}-5\amp\wonder{\gt}-4\amp \substitute{10}-5\amp\wonder{\gt}-4\\
-5\amp\reject{\gt}-4\amp -4\amp\reject{\gt}-4\amp 5\amp\confirm{\gt}-4
\end{aligned}
```]

Everything worked out as expected, so our solution is reasonably checked.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

